The warrior, who spilled a breath snatched in shock, was rendered unconscious by his last words.

It was the Vollachian way to respond to both friendly and hostile attitudes with equal violence - barbarism that would raise the eyebrows of even the emperor of this country.

But no one could stop the boy from doing so.

And that was the most correct thing to do in this imperial fashion.

