At this point, it is necessary to mention a very unfortunate fact about "magic."

This is a different issue from the one described previously, where the Vollachian Empire has developed only physical martial arts and "flow methods" instead of magical techniques.

This is because "Yang magic" and "Yin magic," which have few users among the six magic attributes in this world, are neglected for reasons other than the fact that they are difficult to research.

The Fire attribute manipulates heat to produce flame or even ice.

The Water attribute interferes with the life force of living things, promotes the healing of wounds and illnesses, and saves lives.

The Wind attribute interferes with the atmosphere to regulate the environment and sometimes even ensures survivability in hazardous regions.

The Earth attribute, which manipulates the power of the earth and can either fertilize or starve the land.

Compared to those attributes, each of which has a clear image of the use case, the Yin and Yang attribute is basically considered to be an effect that either enhances or decreases the function of the human body.

While strictly speaking a false understanding, the fact that such an image has taken hold is a major factor in the lack of progress in the development of the respective Yin and Yang magic attributes today.

And perhaps unsurprisingly, it is the "Yang attribute" ――its power to enhance one's abilities that continues to receive a reputation for being out of place and useless.

Knowing the primary effects of yang magic, many may be tempted to question as to why in its evaluation.

However, the more one tries to take advantage of this characteristic, the more there are several very troublesome problems that can not be ignored.

For example, if you look at the effects of yang magic to improve one's physical abilities, in most cases, they were defeated by the enemy without such abilities.

The reason was simple: they could not handle their own enhanced bodies at all, and were unable to use all their strengths, feeling as if they were manipulating someone else's body.

The enhancement of one's abilities may include strengthening the senses, such as eyesight and hearing, enhancing physical abilities, such as arm and leg strength, and strengthening defenses by increasing the density of bones and muscles.

However, warriors always train their own bodies and go into battle knowing their own skills.

Those who received yang magic would throw away their current selves and enter the battlefield in a modified body only with improved performance characteristics. As a result, many of them were defeated and died without being able to do much.

The problem continues to be the fact that the effectiveness of yang magic is greatly affected by the skill of the caster themself, as well as their physical and mental condition that day.

Even if a warrior who has received Yang magic can adapt to his enhanced body, there is no guarantee that he will receive the same enhancement from the same caster tomorrow, or that it will be as effective.

Yang magic is not expected to improve one's ability to fight consistently; on the contrary, it is recognized as a flaw that prevents one from satisfactorily demonstrating one's usual abilities. ――This is the reason why Yang magic has been neglected.

In the past, the Vollachian Empire also had an emperor who focused on the power of magic and wanted to create the most powerful army. The 31st emperor of the Vollachian Empire, Murkia Vollachia, planned to use magic to turn a powerful army into an even more powerful one.

Based on the aforementioned shortcomings, he paired a yang magic user with a strong soldier, trained them so that the enhanced state would be their natural state, and then went into actual battle.

However, the results were disastrous: the strong soldiers, who were supposed to be enhanced, were killed before any yang magic could be applied, the skills of the essential casters were varied, the troops could not function as troops, they were outnumbered, and even the emperor's life was in jeopardy.

The war finally ended when Viva the "Dissector," a close ally of the then-Emperor of Vollachia, defeated the enemy general, but due in part to the magnitude of the defeat, Murkia-Vollachia was given the ignominious nickname of "Emperor of the Great Defeat" As such, the magnitude of the defeat was such that the name was engraved on the history of Murkia Vollachia.

Because of this precedent, the value of yang magic, and thus magic itself, was devalued in Vollachia, leading to the spread of the idea that mastery of martial arts was the sign of a strong soldier.

This has not changed to this day, and Vincent Vollachia, with all his wisdom and ingenuity, has dismissed the use of Yang magic in group battles as something that is beyond consideration.

In fact, when a user of yang magic can only enhance one target at a time, the operation of an army that requires a plurality of soldiers to do the same amount of work is a pipe dream.

Therefore, Yin magic remained as a means of harassment in the sense of inflicting unusual physical effects on the enemy, and magic declined in the Vollachian Empire ――even in other countries, Yang magic was considered an unfavorable discipline that was seldom used except for self-enhancement.

――However, as with everything, exceptions existed.

Subaru: [Let's do it, you guys――!!]

With a large inhale, the boy's voice, still high, was raised in the hills to the west, with the battlefield in the distance.

With the boy at their heart, warriors spread out atop the hill―― a band comprised of no less than several thousand people, who one-by-one raised a banner for the sake of expressing the unity, the will of the group.

A symbol of a will to fight that must never be lowered, the large banner was held aloft by a man to the boy’s side, the former’s body covered in tattoos, supported by a gray lizardman, and a man with a dull appearance yet possessing a dignified look in his eyes.

Depicted on the banner that had been hoisted, recognizable even from a distance, was an insignia with the shape of a star.

It was not the crest of one’s family, neither was it the crest of the nation. Merely the proof of where their hearts lay it was, a declaration of war of sorts and naught else.

The group assembled was a diverse one―― without exaggeration, it was composed of many races.

Even within Vollachia, where a gargantuan number of species lived and coexisted, few relationships in which cooperation was possible even across racial lines. The Demon City of Chaosflame had been one of the few functional cities that posed an exception to that, and even during the siege of the Imperial Capital, there had been no sense of cooperation from the rebels.

But, this group was different.

It was possible to see them as simply working together towards the same purpose. However, this did not mean they could gather under a banner as to brandish a collective will.

It was not that they possessed the same purpose, but that they possessed a shared will.

Hence why this group―― Nay, why the Pleiades Battalion, was able to serve as a trump card.

Spearheading those banners, spearheading the comrades he had gathered, a boy of black hair―― Natsuki Subaru, exclaimed.

Subaru: [――We are, THE STRONGEST!!]

Pleiades: [The strongest! The strongest!! THE STRONGEST!!]

Elevating a war cry in concert, a thunderous roar echoed throughout the heavens, tremendous fighting spirit spreading through the battlefield like tongues of flame.

Beatrice, being held in Subaru's arms as he yelled, covered her ears, her eyes widening in amazement. Likewise, Louis too jumped onto Subaru. Though, only those two young girls were surprised.

Subaru: [――We are, INVINCIBLE!!]

Pleiades: [Invincible! Invincible!! INVINCIBLE!!]

Hiain, Weitz, Idra, Gustav, Orson and the others of his group, Old Man Null, Rex, Milzak, Kashew, Moizo, Deeroy, Creegkin, Codroe, Phenmelle, Jawsrough, Tanza, roared loudly.

The ground quaked as they stamped their feet upon the soil, the quaking beckoning further quaking, rousing their fighting spirit.

In the recesses of his chest, was something ardent.

That ardent, ardent, oh so ardent, trustworthy, irresistible something, coarsed through the entirety of his body.

Placing that ardent, trustworthy, irresistible something atop his tongue――

Subaru: [――OHHHHHHHHHHH INEVITABLE FAAAAAAAATE!!]

Pleiades: [BRING IT ON! BRING IT ON!! BRING IT ON!!!]

The group bellowed in unison, and the eyes of all its members turned to the fore, to the battlefield at the foot of the hill.

And thus――,

Subaru: [――Let’s go.]

